We had problems deploying certain CloudFormation-stacks under unknown circumstances. Replies from the Amazon support hints us to a problem that CFN-Sphere renders JSON templates that may contain empty sections if they are not used in the YAML file. It seems that the Cloud Formation service has problems with empty sections in the JSON-template.

Also the rendered template should be semantically equal to the written yaml-template. The empty sections add semantics which is out of control of the creator of the yaml-template.

Mail from Amazon support:
```
Hello,

Thank you for reaching out regarding the removal of the sections within your 
CloudFormation template file.

To give you a little of background information regarding the CloudFormation 
template, please see the following Template Anatomy:
{
  "AWSTemplateFormatVersion" : "version date",

